This is a micropython directory.

The code here must be run in micropython uploaded to an ESP32 device.
The Adc_async_client is remote and battery powered.
Its purpose is to measure and report on a 3-pack of 18650 Lithium Ion battery cells.
Voltage taps on the cells provides three channels: One cell, Two cells, Three cells.
The server can compute the voltages for each of the three cells in isolation by 
subtraction of the voltage measurements.
The Adc_async_client receives commands via asyncio_connection from the Server running in Python3
The commands originate from the Gui_asyncio_client running on any display host running in Python3. 
The Server receives the commands via asyncio from the Gui_asyncio_client and forwards them to Adc_async_client after adding a unique msgid from a db table (MSGID). (Acts as a generator)
Upon receiving the command, the  Adc_async_client performs a measurement and stores the A2D samples (currently 64) in its flash memory. 
Then it sends via asyncio_connection a message to the Server in which is embedded the A2D samples and other needed fields.
A measurment command (100) will result in 3 measurement reports, each with voltage measurements for ( One cell , Two Cells, Three Cells) respectively.
A calibration command(200) will be for a single channel and will contain the Truth value, vin, (input voltage ). 
A calibration command will result in one calibration_report(201) msg sent to the Server with "vin" embedded along with normal samples and neccessary fields.
The Adc_async_client can receive three commands: Measure (100), Start_Perioc_measurements (175) and Calibrate (200). 
Once Periodic_Measurements are started, Adc_async_client just measures and reports at the specified periods  until the number of repetitions are fulfilled.
For periodic , the Gui_async_client will embed two attributes in msgs thru the Server to the Adc_async_client, Start_Periodic.period and Start_Periodic.repetitions.
The Adc_async_client will send only the following types of reports to the Server:report_measurement(101), report_calibration(201). 
A measurement(100) and a calibration(200) command will vary in two ways: the type ('m','c') and vin = [0, truthValue], where 'm' means measure and 'c' means calibrate, and a calibration is chan specific.
The time expended in ADC client will be ~1 second per channel, or about 3 seconds for all three.
A small amount of time will be expended in translating incoming msgs and formatting outgoing messages.

Summary:
1. Code must run in micropython uploaded to an ESP32.
2. Client must be able to receive commands via json and asyncio
3. Client must be able to report back to Server via json and asyncio.
4. Client must be flexible as to the number of samples, sample_rate, etc.
5. Process latency estimated to be less than 5 seconds round trip from GUI_client -> Svr ->ADC_client.-> Svr -> DB table -> GUI_client.
6. Msg sizes should be less than 1kb.

